(SIREN WAILING)

799
01:31:58,263 --> 01:32:00,174
Okay, you take over.

800
01:32:03,101 --> 01:32:04,933
(ALL CHATTERING)

801
01:32:17,574 --> 01:32:19,360
I love you, Grandpa.

802
01:32:19,534 --> 01:32:21,116
(BABY CRYING)

803
01:32:22,203 --> 01:32:24,911
CONNIE: I'm sorry, Pa.
He doesn't know you yet.

804
01:32:26,332 --> 01:32:29,495
- Hey, big guy. Give it to Grandpa.
- Okay.

805
01:32:29,586 --> 01:32:35,923
"I hope you get well, Grandpa, and wish
I see you soon. Your grandson Frank."

806
01:32:38,845 --> 01:32:41,007
Go with your mother.

807
01:32:41,139 --> 01:32:43,301
Take them downstairs.

808
01:32:49,397 --> 01:32:51,434
Go on, Carlo, you too.

809
01:32:53,151 --> 01:32:55,017
Go on.

810
01:32:58,156 --> 01:32:59,988
(ALL CHATTERING)

811
01:33:15,465 --> 01:33:19,459
- What's the matter with you, Carlo?
- Shut up and set the table.

812
01:33:34,984 --> 01:33:41,026
Since McCluskey's killing, the police
have cracked down on our operations.

813
01:33:42,909 --> 01:33:47,824
And also the other families.
There's been a lot of bad blood.

814
01:33:47,914 --> 01:33:51,248
They hit us, so we hit them back.

815
01:33:52,043 --> 01:33:56,788
Through our newspaper contacts
we've been able to put out material

816
01:33:56,881 --> 01:34:01,000
about McCluskey's link with Sollozzo
in the drug rackets.

817
01:34:01,094 --> 01:34:03,256
So things are loosening up.

818
01:34:04,597 --> 01:34:09,262
And I'm sending Fredo to Las Vegas,

819
01:34:09,394 --> 01:34:12,102
under the protection
of Don Francesco of L.A.

820
01:34:12,230 --> 01:34:16,599
- I want him to rest.
- I'm going to learn the casino business.

821
01:34:24,951 --> 01:34:26,692
(SOFTLY) Where's Michael?

822
01:34:39,132 --> 01:34:42,045
It was Michael who killed Sollozzo.

823
01:34:44,053 --> 01:34:47,842
But he's safe. We're starting to work
to bring him back.

824
01:35:09,078 --> 01:35:11,558
I want you to find out
where that old pimp Tattaglia is hiding.

825
01:35:11,664 --> 01:35:13,575
I want him now.

826
01:35:13,708 --> 01:35:17,121
Sonny, things are starting to loosen up.

827
01:35:17,253 --> 01:35:22,123
If you go after Tattaglia, all hell
will break loose. Pop can negotiate.

828
01:35:22,217 --> 01:35:28,133
He must get better first. I'll decide...
- War is costly. We can't do business.

829
01:35:28,223 --> 01:35:32,182
- Neither can they. Don't worry about it!
- We can't afford a stalemate.

830
01:35:32,310 --> 01:35:37,225
- No more stalemate. I'll kill the bastard!
- You're getting a great reputation!

831
01:35:37,357 --> 01:35:43,148
Do as I say! If I had a Sicilian wartime
<i>consigliere,</i> I wouldn't be in this shape!

832
01:35:43,279 --> 01:35:45,566
Pop had Genco. Look what I got.

833
01:35:49,118 --> 01:35:51,485
I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.

834
01:35:52,622 --> 01:35:55,580
Ma made a little dinner. It's Sunday.

835
01:35:56,542 --> 01:36:01,002
Niggers are having a good time
with our policy banks in Harlem.

836
01:36:01,130 --> 01:36:05,089
Driving new Cadillacs,
paying 50% on a bet.

837
01:36:05,176 --> 01:36:08,589
That's because
they've started making big money.

838
01:36:08,721 --> 01:36:12,055
Papa never talked business
at the table.

839
01:36:12,183 --> 01:36:16,017
- CARLO: Shut up, Connie...
- Don't you ever tell her to shut up.

840
01:36:16,729 --> 01:36:17,764
Don't interfere.

841
01:36:20,191 --> 01:36:24,105
I'd like to talk to you after dinner.
I could do more for the family...

842
01:36:24,195 --> 01:36:26,937
We don't discuss business at the table.

843
01:37:05,820 --> 01:37:07,185
(HORN HONKS)

844
01:37:14,203 --> 01:37:16,661
(IN ITALIAN)
I kiss your hand, Don Tommasino.

845
01:37:22,420 --> 01:37:24,411
Why are you so far
from the house?

846
01:37:24,964 --> 01:37:27,581
You know I'm responsible to your
father for your life.

847
01:37:27,675 --> 01:37:29,040
The bodyguards are here.

848
01:37:29,886 --> 01:37:31,968
It's still dangerous...

849
01:37:32,263 --> 01:37:35,381
We've heard from Santino
in New York...

850
01:37:35,475 --> 01:37:37,762
Your enemies know you're here.

851
01:37:38,895 --> 01:37:42,229
Did Santino say when
I can go back?

852
01:37:42,315 --> 01:37:43,976
Not yet.

853
01:37:44,275 --> 01:37:46,061
It's out of the question.

854
01:37:49,405 --> 01:37:50,895
Where are you going now?

855
01:37:52,450 --> 01:37:53,565
To Corleone.

856
01:37:54,327 --> 01:37:55,408
Take my car.

857
01:37:58,831 --> 01:37:59,866
I want to walk.

858
01:38:02,668 --> 01:38:03,829
Be careful.

859
01:38:18,476 --> 01:38:19,841
(BELL TOLLING)

860
01:38:23,940 --> 01:38:25,522
Michael. Corleone.

861
01:38:38,246 --> 01:38:39,846
(IN ITALIAN)
Where have all the men gone?

862
01:38:40,540 --> 01:38:42,827
They're all dead from vendettas.

863
01:38:44,335 --> 01:38:46,827
There are the names of the dead.

864
01:39:03,354 --> 01:39:07,268
Hey, hey, take me to the America, G.I.!

865
01:39:07,358 --> 01:39:11,773
Hey, hey, take me to the America, G.I.!
Clark Gable!

866
01:39:11,904 --> 01:39:17,195
America! Take me to the America, G.I.!
Clark Gable, Rita Hayworth!

867
01:39:17,326 --> 01:39:19,363
(GRUMBLING IN ITALIAN)

868
01:39:20,830 --> 01:39:22,446
(WOMEN SINGING)

869
01:39:35,052 --> 01:39:37,168
(IN ITALIAN) Mamma mia what a beauty.

870
01:39:37,263 --> 01:39:38,845
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

871
01:39:45,396 --> 01:39:48,479
I think you got hit
by the thunderbolt.

872
01:39:54,447 --> 01:39:58,441
(IN ITALIAN) In Sicily women are more
dangerous than shotguns.

873
01:40:10,588 --> 01:40:12,204
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

874
01:40:21,849 --> 01:40:23,465
Did you have a good hunt?

875
01:40:24,477 --> 01:40:26,639
