01:48:46,979 --> 01:48:50,438
If you touch my sister again,
I'll kill you.

941
01:49:05,372 --> 01:49:06,407
(BELL TOLLING)

942
01:49:06,498 --> 01:49:08,205
(RECITING IN LATIN)

943
01:49:11,045 --> 01:49:13,457
(BAND PLAYING TRADITIONAL MUSIC)

944
01:49:18,886 --> 01:49:20,422
(ALL APPLAUDING)

945
01:50:37,965 --> 01:50:39,501
(ALL APPLAUDING)

946
01:52:43,674 --> 01:52:47,963
Hey! We weren't expecting you, Kay.
You should call.

947
01:52:48,095 --> 01:52:52,259
Yes, I have.
I've tried writing and calling.

948
01:52:52,349 --> 01:52:56,138
- I want to reach Michael.
Nobody knows where he is.

949
01:52:56,270 --> 01:52:58,932
All we know is that he's all right.

950
01:53:01,358 --> 01:53:05,147
- What was that?
- An accident, but nobody was hurt.

951
01:53:06,321 --> 01:53:10,155
Tom, will you give this letter to Michael.
Please?

952
01:53:11,827 --> 01:53:17,118
If I accepted that, a court could prove
I have knowledge of his whereabouts.

953
01:53:18,041 --> 01:53:19,952
He'll get in touch with you.

954
01:53:20,043 --> 01:53:23,707
I let my cab go,
so can I call another one, please?

955
01:53:23,797 --> 01:53:25,583
Come on. Sorry.

956
01:53:32,723 --> 01:53:34,339
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

957
01:53:42,941 --> 01:53:47,435
<i>- Hello?
- WOMAN: Is Carla there?</i>

958
01:53:48,196 --> 01:53:50,813
- Who is this?
- <i>A friend of Carlo.</i>

959
01:53:50,949 --> 01:53:54,408
<i>Tell him that I can't make it tonight
untll later.</i>

960
01:54:00,042 --> 01:54:01,407
Bitch!

961
01:54:03,420 --> 01:54:06,162
- Dinner's on the table.
- I'm not hungry.

962
01:54:06,256 --> 01:54:09,419
- The food is getting cold.
- I'll eat out later.

963
01:54:09,551 --> 01:54:13,010
- You just told me to make you dinner!
- <i>Vafangool!</i>

964
01:54:13,263 --> 01:54:15,425
I'll <i>vafangool</i> you!

965
01:54:20,228 --> 01:54:22,970
She has a filthy mouth, this Guinea brat.

966
01:54:27,319 --> 01:54:31,563
That's it, break it all,
you spoiled Guinea brat. Break it all!

967
01:54:40,832 --> 01:54:43,995
Why don't you bring
your whore home for dinner?

968
01:54:45,003 --> 01:54:46,585
Maybe I will.

969
01:54:53,261 --> 01:54:56,470
- Clean it up!
- Like hell I will!

970
01:54:56,598 --> 01:55:00,466
You skinny, spoiled brat.
Clean it up! Clean it up!

971
01:55:00,602 --> 01:55:05,142
Clean it up! I said, clean it up!
Clean it up!

972
01:55:05,315 --> 01:55:10,105
Clean it up. Clean that up, you...

973
01:55:13,365 --> 01:55:15,072
Clean it!

974
01:55:15,158 --> 01:55:19,447
Clean it up! Yeah, kill me.
Be a murderer, like your father!

975
01:55:19,538 --> 01:55:22,872
- All you Corleones are murderers!
- I hate you!

976
01:55:23,041 --> 01:55:24,657
Come on, kill me!

977
01:55:26,336 --> 01:55:27,918
Get out of here!

978
01:55:28,046 --> 01:55:31,289
- I hate you!
- Now I'll kill you.

979
01:55:31,425 --> 01:55:34,258
You Guinea brat. Get out of here!

980
01:55:37,556 --> 01:55:39,342
(CONNIE SCREAMING)

981
01:55:44,563 --> 01:55:47,521
Connie, what's the matter?
I can't hear you.

982
01:55:48,692 --> 01:55:51,730
Connie, talk louder. The baby's crying.

983
01:55:51,862 --> 01:55:54,399
Santino, I can't understand.
I don't know.

984
01:55:54,531 --> 01:55:55,646
(SHUSHING)

985
01:55:56,116 --> 01:55:57,777
Yeah, Connie.

986
01:55:58,410 --> 01:55:59,992
(CRYING CONTINUES)

987
01:56:02,456 --> 01:56:04,413
You wait there.

988
01:56:07,169 --> 01:56:09,627
No, you just wait there.

989
01:56:11,840 --> 01:56:14,127
Son-of-a-bitch.

990
01:56:14,259 --> 01:56:17,468
- Son-of-a-bitch!
- What's the matter?

991
01:56:21,433 --> 01:56:24,516
Open the goddamn gate!
Get off your ass.

992
01:56:32,527 --> 01:56:33,858
Sonny!

993
01:56:40,410 --> 01:56:42,401
- Sonny.
- Get out of here!

994
01:56:43,538 --> 01:56:45,370
Go after him, go on!

995
01:56:58,386 --> 01:57:00,093
(HORN HONKING)

996
01:57:04,559 --> 01:57:06,095
(TOLL BELL DINGS)

997
01:57:07,229 --> 01:57:09,220
(MAN CHATTERING ON RADIO)

998
01:57:15,028 --> 01:57:17,019
Son-of-a-bitch. Come on!

999
01:57:17,155 --> 01:57:18,691
(HORN BLARING)

1000
01:57:18,782 --> 01:57:20,398
(COIN CLINKING)

1001
01:57:39,261 --> 01:57:40,626
(SCREAMING)

1002
01:57:55,610 --> 01:57:57,192
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1003
01:58:04,160 --> 01:58:05,742
(CARS DRIVING OFF)

1004
01:59:05,680 --> 01:59:07,717
Give me a drop.

1005
01:59:16,066 --> 01:59:18,353
My wife is crying upstairs.

1006
01:59:20,612 --> 01:59:23,274
I hear cars coming to the house.

1007
01:59:27,827 --> 01:59:30,694
<i>Consigliere</i> of mine,

1008
01:59:30,830 --> 01:59:34,448
tell your Don
what everyone seems to know.

1009
01:59:34,542 --> 01:59:36,749
I didn't tell Mama anything.

1010
01:59:37,712 --> 01:59:41,046
I was about to come up and wake you
and tell you.

1011
01:59:44,678 --> 01:59:46,669
But you needed a drink first.

1012
01:59:49,099 --> 01:59:50,385
Yeah.

1013
01:59:53,770 --> 01:59:56,137
Well, now you've had your drink.

1014
02:00:01,569 --> 02:00:05,688
They shot Sonny on the causeway.
He's dead.

1015
02:00:22,757 --> 02:00:25,169
I want no inquiries made.

1016
02:00:29,764 --> 02:00:32,176
I want no acts of vengeance.

1017
02:00:33,810 --> 02:00:36,598
I want you to arrange a meeting

1018
02:00:37,605 --> 02:00:40,393
with the heads of the five families.

1019
02:00:42,318 --> 02:00:44,400
This war stops now.

1020
02:01:06,342 --> 02:01:08,754
Call Bonasera.

1021
02:01:08,887 --> 02:01:11,094
I need him now.

1022
02:01:23,568 --> 02:01:28,779
This is Tom Hagen. I'm calling
for Vito Corleone, at his request.

1023
02:01:28,865 --> 02:01:31,152
You owe your Don a service.

1024
02:01:31,242 --> 02:01:34,735
<i>He has no doubt that you will repay it.</i>

1025
02:01:34,829 --> 02:01:39,198
<i>He will be at your funeral parlor
in one hour. Be there to greet him.</i>

1026
02:02:00,438 --> 02:02:05,183
Well, my friend, are you ready
to do me this service?

1027
02:02:05,276 --> 02:02:08,394
Yes. What do you want me to do?

1028
02:02:16,830 --> 02:02:21,199
I want you to use all your powers
and all your skills.

1029
02:02:25,421 --> 02:02:28,334
I don't want his mother
to see him this way.

1030
02:02:44,399 --> 02:02:47,482
Look how they massacred my boy.

1031
02:02:58,204 --> 02:03:00,070
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1032
02:03:08,631 --> 02:03:10,292
(APOLLONIA LAUGHING)

1033
02:03:15,430 --> 02:03:16,465
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1034
02:03:16,556 --> 02:03:19,924
It's safer to teach you English!

1035
02:03:20,518 --> 02:03:21,849
I know English...

1036
02:03:21,936 --> 02:03:26,931
Monday, Tuesday, Thursday,
Wednesday, Friday, Sunday, Saturday.

1037
02:03:33,907 --> 02:03:35,898
Greetings, Don Tommasino.

1038
02:03:36,534 --> 02:03:38,525
How are things in Palermo?

1039
02:03:44,584 --> 02:03:48,669
Michael is teaching me to
drive... watch, I'll show you.

1040
02:03:51,341 --> 02:03:53,127
How are things in Palermo?

1041
02:03:53,676 --> 02:03:56,794
Young people don't respect
anything anymore...

1042
02:03:57,889 --> 02:04:01,098
times are changing for the worse.

1043
02:04:03,394 --> 02:04:06,932
This place has become
too dangerous for you.

1044
02:04:09,567 --> 02:04:14,812
I want you to move to a villa
near Siracusa... right now.

1045
02:04:20,787 --> 02:04:21,948
What's wrong?

1046
02:04:22,914 --> 02:04:25,155
Bad news from America.

1047
02:04:27,752 --> 02:04:31,416
Your brother, Santino,
they killed him.

1048
02:04:35,009 --> 02:04:36,591
(CAR HONKING)

1049
02:04:37,887 --> 02:04:39,924
Let's go... you promised.

1050
02:04:58,658 --> 02:04:59,739
Fabrizio!

1051
02:04:59,826 --> 02:05:01,032
(IN ITALIAN) Get the car.

1052
02:05:02,537 --> 02:05:06,747
Are you driving yourself, Boss?
Is your wife coming with you?

1053
02:05:06,833 --> 02:05:10,042
No, take her to her father's house
until things are safe.

1054
02:05:10,420 --> 02:05:12,331
Okay, anything you say.

1055
02:05:18,261 --> 02:05:19,922
(IN ITALIAN) Calo, where is Apollonia?

1056
02:05:20,847 --> 02:05:24,260
She's going to surprise you.
She wants to drive.

1057
02:05:26,602 --> 02:05:28,684
She'll make a good American wife.

1058
02:05:29,981 --> 02:05:32,643
Wait, I'll get the baggage.

1059
02:05:42,994 --> 02:05:44,951
Fabrizio!

1060
02:05:45,121 --> 02:05:46,907
(IN ITALIAN) Where are you going?

1061
02:05:47,040 --> 02:05:48,280
(CAR HONKING)

1062
02:05:48,499 --> 02:05:50,991
Wait there! I'll drive to you.

1063
02:05:56,966 --> 02:05:58,582
No, Apollonia!

1064
02:06:21,532 --> 02:06:27,403
VITO: Don Barzini, I want to thank you
for helping me organize this meeting,

1065
02:06:27,497 --> 02:06:32,242
and the other heads of the five families
from New York and New Jersey.

1066
02:06:34,003 --> 02:06:37,166
Carmine Cuneo from the Bronx,

1067
02:06:37,256 --> 02:06:40,624
and from Brooklyn

1068
02:06:42,220 --> 02:06:44,302
Philip Tattaglia.

1069
02:06:46,015 --> 02:06:48,928
And from Staten Island

1070
02:06:49,060 --> 02:06:52,394
we have with us Victor Strachi.

1071
02:06:52,480 --> 02:06:58,021
And the other associates that came as
far as from California and Kansas City

1072
02:06:58,194 --> 02:07:02,062
and all the other territories
of the country. Thank you.

1073
02:07:08,871 --> 02:07:12,205
How did things ever get so far?

1074
02:07:12,291 --> 02:07:14,077
I don't know.

1075
02:07:16,129 --> 02:07:19,497
It was so unfortunate, so unnecessary.

1076
02:07:22,677 --> 02:07:26,011
Tattaglia lost a son, and I lost a son.

1077
02:07:28,516 --> 02:07:32,054
We're quits. And if Tattaglia agrees,

1078
02:07:32,145 --> 02:07:36,139
then I'm willing to let things go on
as before.

1079
02:07:37,483 --> 02:07:41,021
We're grateful to Don Corleone
for calling this meeting.

1080
02:07:41,112 --> 02:07:46,653
We all know him as a man of his word.
A modest man who listens to reason.

1081
02:07:46,742 --> 02:07:50,861
Yes, Don Barzini. He's too modest.

1082
02:07:50,955 --> 02:07:54,994
He had all the judges and politicians
in his pocket.

1083
02:07:55,084 --> 02:07:57,951
He refused to share them.

1084
02:07:58,045 --> 02:08:02,004
When did I ever refuse
an accommodation?

1085
02:08:02,133 --> 02:08:04,295
All of you know me.

1086
02:08:05,261 --> 02:08:10,472
When did I ever refuse,
except one time? And Why?

1087
02:08:12,059 --> 02:08:18,101
Because I believe this drug business
will destroy us in the years to come.

1088
02:08:18,191 --> 02:08:22,276
It's not like gambling or liquor
or even women,

1089
02:08:22,361 --> 02:08:28,357
which is something that most people
want, but is forbidden by the Church.

1090
02:08:28,492 --> 02:08:33,077
Even the police that have helped us in
the past with gambling and other things

1091
02:08:33,164 --> 02:08:37,499
are going to refuse to help us
when it comes to narcotics.

1092
02:08:37,585 --> 02:08:42,705
I believed that then
and I believe that now.

1093
02:08:42,798 --> 02:08:45,130
Times have changed.

1094
02:08:45,218 --> 02:08:49,928
It's not like the old days,
when we could do anything we wanted.

1095
02:08:50,014 --> 02:08:52,847
A refusal is not the act of a friend.

1096
02:08:52,975 --> 02:08:58,220
If Don Corleone had all the judges and
politicians, then he must share them

1097
02:08:58,356 --> 02:09:03,066
or let others use them. He must let us
draw the water from the well.

1098
02:09:04,153 --> 02:09:07,646
Certainly he can present a bill
for such services.

1099
02:09:07,782 --> 02:09:10,240
After all, we're not communists.

1100
02:09:13,371 --> 02:09:16,580
I also don't believe in drugs.

1101
02:09:16,666 --> 02:09:21,251
For years I paid my people extra, so
they wouldn't do that kind of business.

1102
02:09:21,587 --> 02:09:24,750
Somebody says to them
"I have powders."

1103
02:09:24,840 --> 02:09:28,253
"If you put up
3-4,000 dollar investment,

1104
02:09:28,386 --> 02:09:30,969
we can make 50,000 distributing."

1105
02:09:32,223 --> 02:09:38,219
They can't resist. I want to control it
as a business, keep it respectable.

1106
02:09:38,354 --> 02:09:43,099
I don't want it near schools,
I don't want it sold to children.

1107
02:09:43,192 --> 02:09:45,183
That's an <i>infàmia.</i>

1108
02:09:46,362 --> 02:09:50,230
In my city we would keep the traffic
to the colored.

1109
02:09:50,366 --> 02:09:53,575
They're animals,
so let them lose their souls.

1110
02:10:00,334 --> 02:10:03,827
I hoped that we could come here
and reason together.

1111
02:10:05,339 --> 02:10:11,881
And I'm willing to do whatever is
necessary to find a peaceful solution.

1112
02:10:12,388 --> 02:10:17,053
We are agreed. The traffic in drugs
will be permitted, but controlled.

1113
02:10:17,143 --> 02:10:21,307
Don Corleone will give us protection
in the east, and there will be peace.

1114
02:10:21,439 --> 02:10:25,103
I must have strict assurance
from Corleone.

1115
02:10:25,192 --> 02:10:28,605
As time goes by
and his position becomes stronger,

1116
02:10:28,696 --> 02:10:31,233
will he attempt any individual vendetta?

1117
02:10:31,324 --> 02:10:36,535
BARZINI: We are all reasonable men.
We don't have to give assurances.

1118
02:10:36,662 --> 02:10:39,495
You talk about vengeance.

1119
02:10:39,623 --> 02:10:42,911
Will vengeance
bring your son back to you?

1120
02:10:43,044 --> 02:10:45,411
Or my boy to me?

1121
02:10:45,504 --> 02:10:48,246
I forgo the vengeance of my son.

1122
02:10:51,260 --> 02:10:53,422
But I have selfish reasons.

1123
02:10:55,723 --> 02:10:59,216
My youngest son was forced
to leave this country

1124
02:11:01,270 --> 02:11:03,728
because of this Sollozzo business.

1125
02:11:05,232 --> 02:11:09,021
And I have to make arrangements
to bring him back here safely.

1126
02:11:09,320 --> 02:11:11,982
Cleared of all these false charges.

1127
02:11:13,282 --> 02:11:16,525
But I'm a superstitious man.

1128
02:11:16,660 --> 02:11:21,951
If an unlucky accident should befall him,
if he should be shot by a police officer,

1129
02:11:23,250 --> 02:11:26,959
or if he should hang himself
in his jail cell,

1130
02:11:27,088 --> 02:11:29,876
or if he's struck by a bolt of lightning,

1131
02:11:31,217 --> 02:11:34,710
then I'm going to blame
some of the people in this room.

1132
02:11:36,263 --> 02:11:38,675
And that I do not forgive.

1133
02:11:41,310 --> 02:11:43,517
But, that aside,

1134
02:11:46,607 --> 02:11:49,099
let me say that I swear

1135
02:11:50,528 --> 02:11:53,691
on the souls of my grandchildren,

1136
02:11:53,864 --> 02:11:58,279
that I will not be the one to break
the peace we've made here today.

1137
02:12:23,686 --> 02:12:29,272
Should I insist that all of Tattaglia's
drug middlemen have clean records?

1138
02:12:29,358 --> 02:12:31,474
Mention it. Don't insist.

1139
02:12:33,487 --> 02:12:38,357
- Barzini will know without being told.
- You mean Tattaglia.

1140
02:12:39,910 --> 02:12:41,867
Tattaglia's a pimp.

1141
02:12:42,955 --> 02:12:46,118
He could never have outfought Santino.

1142
02:12:48,335 --> 02:12:54,081
But I didn't know until this day
that it was Barzini all along.

1143
02:13:09,398 --> 02:13:11,514
Come on, Nancy.

1144
02:13:12,776 --> 02:13:15,518
Keep together, everyone. Brian.

1145
02:13:16,697 --> 02:13:18,529
Okay, all right.

1146
02:13:31,337 --> 02:13:33,578
How long have you been back?

1147
02:13:34,340 --> 02:13:36,377
I've been back a year.

1148
02:13:37,635 --> 02:13:39,797
Longer than that, I think.

1149
02:13:42,598 --> 02:13:44,805
It's good to see you, Kay.

1150
02:13:55,819 --> 02:13:58,481
I'm working for my father now, Kay.

1151
02:14:00,866 --> 02:14:03,858
He's been sick. Very sick.

1152
02:14:05,579 --> 02:14:07,490
But you're not like him.

1153
02:14:07,623 --> 02:14:11,366
You told me you weren't going to
become like your father.

1154
02:14:13,295 --> 02:14:17,414
My father is no different
than any other powerful man.

1155
02:14:17,550 --> 02:14:21,168
Any man who's responsible
for other people.

1156
02:14:22,388 --> 02:14:24,675
Like a senator or president.

1157
02:14:24,807 --> 02:14:27,390
- How naive you sound.
- Why?

1158
02:14:27,476 --> 02:14:30,218
They don't have men killed.

1159
02:14:33,482 --> 02:14:35,473
Who's being naive, Kay?

1160
02:14:36,610 --> 02:14:40,899
My father's way of doing things is over.
Even he knows that.

1161
02:14:42,616 --> 02:14:46,826
In five years the Corleone family
is going to be completely legitimate.

1162
02:14:48,622 --> 02:14:52,581
Trust me. That's all I can tell you
about my business. Kay...

1163
02:14:54,086 --> 02:14:57,249
Michael, why did you come here? Why?

1164
02:14:58,424 --> 02:15:03,464
What do you want with me after all
this time? I've been calling and writing.

1165
02:15:03,554 --> 02:15:06,922
I came because I need you.
I care for you.

1166
02:15:07,057 --> 02:15:10,846
- Please stop it, Michael.
- Because... I want you to marry me.

1167
02:15:12,438 --> 02:15:15,226
- It's too late.
- Please, Kay...

1168
02:15:16,859 --> 02:15:20,727
I'll do anything you ask
to make up for what's happened to us.

1169
02:15:22,531 --> 02:15:26,866
Because that's important, Kay.
Because what's important is that

1170
02:15:28,537 --> 02:15:31,620
we have each other.
That we have a life together.

1171
02:15:33,334 --> 02:15:35,951
That we have children. Our children.

1172
02:15:37,588 --> 02:15:39,545
Kay, I need you.

1173
02:15:41,508 --> 02:15:43,249
And I love you.

1174
02:16:05,366 --> 02:16:09,155
TESSIO: Barzini's people chisel
my territory and we do nothing about it!

1175
02:16:09,286 --> 02:16:12,779
- Soon I'll have no place to hang my hat!
- MICHAEL: Be patient.

1176
02:16:12,915 --> 02:16:16,078
TESSIO: I'm not asking for help.
Just take off the handcuffs.

1177
02:16:16,168 --> 02:16:19,331
MICHAEL: Be patient.
CARLO: We must protect ourselves.

1178
02:16:19,421 --> 02:16:22,755
- Let me recruit some new men.
- MICHAEL: No.

1179
02:16:22,883 --> 02:16:26,717
- Barzini would get an excuse to fight.
- TESSIO: Mike, you're wrong.

1180
02:16:28,305 --> 02:16:30,546
CLEMENZA: Don Corleone...

1181
02:16:30,683 --> 02:16:34,517
You once said that one day Tessio
and me could form our own family.

1182
02:16:34,645 --> 02:16:38,684
Till today I would never think of it.
I must ask your permission.

1183
02:16:39,692 --> 02:16:42,559
Michael is now head of the family.

1184
02:16:42,695 --> 02:16:46,734
If he gives his permission,
then you have my blessing.

1185
02:16:46,865 --> 02:16:49,357
After we make the move to Nevada

1186
02:16:49,493 --> 02:16:53,703
you can leave the Corleone family
and go on your own.

1187
02:16:53,789 --> 02:16:58,204
- TESSIO: How long will that be?
- Six months.

1188
02:16:58,335 --> 02:17:01,418
Forgive me, but with you gone,

1189
02:17:01,505 --> 02:17:04,543
me and Pete
will come under Barzini's thumb.

1190
02:17:04,633 --> 02:17:10,219
I hate that Barzini. In six months' time
there will be nothing left to build on.

1191
02:17:10,347 --> 02:17:13,214
- Do you have faith in my judgment?
- Yes.

1192
02:17:13,350 --> 02:17:16,217
- Do I have your loyalty?
- Always, Godfather.

1193
02:17:16,395 --> 02:17:19,729
Then be a friend to Michael.
Do as he says.

1194
02:17:24,570 --> 02:17:29,781
Things are negotiated that'll solve your
problems and answer your questions.

1195
02:17:29,908 --> 02:17:32,240
That's all I can tell you now.

1196
02:17:33,036 --> 02:17:35,573
Carlo, you grew up in Nevada.

1197
02:17:35,706 --> 02:17:39,119
When we make our move there,
you'll be my right-hand man.

1198
02:17:39,209 --> 02:17:43,954
Tom Hagen is no longer <i>consigliere.</i>
He'll be our lawyer in Vegas.

1199
02:17:44,047 --> 02:17:46,630
That's no reflection on Tom,
just how I want it.

1200
02:17:46,759 --> 02:17:51,469
If I ever need help, who's a better
<i>consigliere</i> than my father? That's it.

1201
02:18:11,533 --> 02:18:15,322
- Thank you, Papa.
- I'm happy for you, Carlo.

1202
02:18:15,412 --> 02:18:18,245
Mike... Why am I out?

1203
02:18:19,625 --> 02:18:22,583
You're not a wartime <i>consigliere,</i> Tom.

1204
02:18:23,712 --> 02:18:27,000
Things may get rough with the move.

1205
02:18:27,132 --> 02:18:28,463
Tom.

1206
02:18:33,680 --> 02:18:38,641
I advised Michael. I never thought
you were a bad <i>consigliere.</i>

1207
02:18:38,769 --> 02:18:42,933
I thought Santino was a bad Don,
rest in peace.

1208
02:18:44,483 --> 02:18:47,771
Michael has all my confidence,
just as you do.

1209
02:18:48,695 --> 02:18:53,690
But there are reasons why you must
have no part in what is going to happen.

1210
02:18:54,785 --> 02:18:57,823
Maybe I could help.
- You're out, Tom.

1211
02:19:07,798 --> 02:19:09,414
(DOOR CLOSING)

1212
02:19:46,879 --> 02:19:51,294
I can't get over the way your face looks.
So good!

1213
02:19:51,425 --> 02:19:55,840
This doctor did some job.
Did Kay talk you into it? Hey, hey, hey!

1214
02:19:55,929 --> 02:20:00,093
Leave them out here.
He's tired and wants to clean up.

1215
02:20:00,225 --> 02:20:02,637
Let me open the door, all right?

1216
02:20:03,896 --> 02:20:06,638
(PLAYING
<i>FOR HE'S A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW)</i>

1217
02:20:08,859 --> 02:20:14,150
- Hello, Mike! Welcome to Las Vegas!
- All for you, kid! It's all his idea.

1218
02:20:14,281 --> 02:20:16,739
JOHNNY: Your brother Freddy.
FREDO: Girls?

1219
02:20:20,704 --> 02:20:23,742
I'll be right back. Keep them occupied.

1220
02:20:25,083 --> 02:20:28,701
- Anything you want, kid, anything.
- Who are the girls?

1221
02:20:29,963 --> 02:20:33,456
- That's for you to find out.
Get rid of them, Fredo.

1222
02:20:34,885 --> 02:20:39,721
- Hey, Mike...
- I'm here on business. Get rid of them.

1223
02:20:39,806 --> 02:20:42,389
I'm tired. Get rid of the band too.

1224
02:20:48,273 --> 02:20:51,265
Hey, take off. Take off. Let's go.

1225
02:20:51,735 --> 02:20:53,817
Hey, that's it. Hey, Angelo.

1226
02:20:55,530 --> 02:20:57,612
Hey, come on! Scram!

1227
02:20:59,284 --> 02:21:02,743
Come on, honey. I don't know
what's the matter with him, Johnny.

1228
02:21:02,871 --> 02:21:04,236
Sorry.

1229
02:21:06,124 --> 02:21:08,786
I don't know. He's tired.

1230
02:21:14,299 --> 02:21:15,710
(DOOR CLOSING)

1231
02:21:15,801 --> 02:21:18,668
What happened to Moe Greene?

1232
02:21:18,762 --> 02:21:23,222
He had some business. He said to
give him a call when the party started.

1233
02:21:23,350 --> 02:21:25,216
Well, give him a call.

1234
02:21:26,645 --> 02:21:29,854
- Johnny, how are you?
- Nice to see you, Mike.

1235
02:21:29,982 --> 02:21:31,973
MICHAEL: We're proud of you.
JOHNNY: Thanks.

1236
02:21:32,109 --> 02:21:35,852
Sit down, I want to talk to you.
The Don is proud too.

1237
02:21:35,988 --> 02:21:37,979
Well, I owe it all to him.

1238
02:21:39,199 --> 02:21:40,860
He knows how grateful you are.

1239
02:21:40,951 --> 02:21:44,160
That's why
he'd like to ask a favor of you.

1240
02:21:44,246 --> 02:21:46,157
Mike, what can I do?

1241
02:21:47,374 --> 02:21:49,911
We're thinking of giving up our interests

1242
02:21:50,043 --> 02:21:52,876
in the olive oil business
and settling here.

1243
02:21:53,672 --> 02:21:58,917
Moe will sell us his share of the casino
and the hotel, so we'll own all of it.

1244
02:21:59,011 --> 02:22:01,719
- Tom!
- Are you sure?

1245
02:22:01,805 --> 02:22:04,797
Moe loves the business.
He never said nothing about selling.

1246
02:22:04,933 --> 02:22:07,800
I'll make him an offer he can't refuse.

1247
02:22:08,854 --> 02:22:11,437
See, Johnny...

1248
02:22:11,565 --> 02:22:15,684
We figure that entertainment
would draw gamblers to the casino.

1249
02:22:15,819 --> 02:22:19,608
We hope you'll sign a contract
to appear five times a year.

1250
02:22:22,492 --> 02:22:27,032
Perhaps convince some of your friends
in the movies to do the same.

1251
02:22:28,373 --> 02:22:30,489
We're counting on you.

1252
02:22:32,502 --> 02:22:36,086
Sure, Mike.
I'll do anything for my godfather.

1253
02:22:36,214 --> 02:22:37,579
Good.

1254
02:22:39,092 --> 02:22:43,882
Hey, Mike! Hello, fellows.
Everybody's here. Freddy, Tom.

1255
02:22:44,014 --> 02:22:46,472
Good to see you.
- How are you, Moe?

1256
02:22:46,600 --> 02:22:51,686
Have everything? Specially prepared
food, the best dancers, and good credit.

1257
02:22:51,813 --> 02:22:55,272
Draw chips for everybody,
so they can play on the house.

1258
02:22:57,861 --> 02:23:00,728
Is my credit good enough
to buy you out?

1259
02:23:02,491 --> 02:23:04,277
Buy me out?

1260
02:23:04,409 --> 02:23:06,867
The casino, the hotel.

1261
02:23:06,995 --> 02:23:09,862
The Corleone family
wants to buy you out.

1262
02:23:09,998 --> 02:23:15,493
The Corleone family wants
to buy me out? No, I buy you out.

1263
02:23:15,629 --> 02:23:18,872
Your casino loses money.
We can do better.

1264
02:23:19,007 --> 02:23:23,092
- You think I'm skimming off the top?
- You're unlucky.

1265
02:23:27,766 --> 02:23:30,133
You Guineas make me laugh.

1266
02:23:30,268 --> 02:23:34,978
I took Freddy in when you had a bad
time, and now you try to push me out!

1267
02:23:36,149 --> 02:23:39,767
You did that
because we bankrolled your casino

1268
02:23:39,903 --> 02:23:44,943
and the Molinari family guaranteed
his safety. Let's talk business.

1269
02:23:45,075 --> 02:23:47,988
Yes. First of all, you're all done.

1270
02:23:48,120 --> 02:23:50,452
You don't have
that kind of muscle anymore.

1271
02:23:50,539 --> 02:23:54,874
The Godfather is sick. You're getting
chased out of New York by the others.

1272
02:23:54,960 --> 02:23:58,999
Do you think you can come to my hotel
and take over?

1273
02:23:59,131 --> 02:24:03,921
I talked to Barzini. I can make a deal
with him and still keep my hotel!

1274
02:24:04,052 --> 02:24:07,670
Is that why you slapped my brother
around in public?

1275
02:24:07,764 --> 02:24:12,554
That was nothing, Mike.
Moe didn't mean nothing by that.

1276
02:24:12,686 --> 02:24:16,930
He flies off the handle sometimes,
but we're good friends.

1277
02:24:17,023 --> 02:24:21,733
I have a business to run.
We got to kick asses sometimes.

1278
02:24:21,820 --> 02:24:25,688
We had an argument,
so I had to straighten him out.

1279
02:24:25,782 --> 02:24:28,570
You straightened my brother out?

1280
02:24:28,702 --> 02:24:32,991
He was banging cocktail waitresses!
Players couldn't get a drink.

1281
02:24:33,123 --> 02:24:34,989
What's wrong with you?

1282
02:24:40,172 --> 02:24:42,880
I leave for New York tomorrow.
Think about a price.

1283
02:24:42,966 --> 02:24:44,081
(DRINK SPILLING)

1284
02:24:44,176 --> 02:24:45,758
Son-of-a-bitch!

1285
02:24:45,844 --> 02:24:51,055
I'm Moe Greene! I made my bones
when you were out with cheerleaders.

1286
02:24:51,183 --> 02:24:53,550
Wait a minute, Moe. I have an idea.

1287
02:24:54,644 --> 02:24:58,182
Tom, you're the <i>consigliere.</i>
Talk to the Don...

1288
02:24:58,315 --> 02:25:03,776
Just a minute. Don is semi-retired and
Mike is in charge of the family business.

1289
02:25:03,862 --> 02:25:07,025
If you have anything to say,
say it to Michael.

1290
02:25:10,118 --> 02:25:11,153
(DOOR SLAMMING)

1291
02:25:12,204 --> 02:25:16,949
Mike, you don't come to Las Vegas and
talk to a man like Moe Greene like that!

1292
02:25:17,626 --> 02:25:18,866
Fredo...

1293
02:25:20,170 --> 02:25:22,832
You're my older brother, and I love you.

1294
02:25:24,174 --> 02:25:28,168
But don't ever take sides with anyone
against the family again.

1295
02:25:29,804 --> 02:25:31,044
Ever.

1296
02:25:39,022 --> 02:25:43,186
I have to see my father and his people,
so have dinner without me.

1297
02:25:44,903 --> 02:25:49,693
This weekend we'll go out. We'll go to
the city, see a show and have dinner.

1298
02:25:57,249 --> 02:26:00,037
Your sister wants to ask you something.

1299
02:26:00,168 --> 02:26:02,284
- Let her ask.
- She's afraid to.

1300
02:26:02,420 --> 02:26:05,378
They want you to be godfather
to their boy.

1301
02:26:05,465 --> 02:26:07,251
- We'll see.
- Will you?

1302
02:26:07,384 --> 02:26:09,716
Let me think about it. Come on.

1303
02:26:18,520 --> 02:26:21,433
Barzini will move against you first.

1304
02:26:21,523 --> 02:26:26,063
He'll set up a meeting with someone
you absolutely trust.

1305
02:26:26,152 --> 02:26:28,234
Guaranteeing your safety.

1306
02:26:29,281 --> 02:26:32,319
And at that meeting
you'll be assassinated.

1307
02:26:37,080 --> 02:26:40,072
I like to drink wine more than I used to.

1308
02:26:41,543 --> 02:26:45,207
- Anyway, I'm drinking more.
- It's good for you, Pop.

1309
02:26:50,302 --> 02:26:51,667
I don't know.

1310
02:26:53,722 --> 02:26:56,589
Are you happy with your wife
and children?

1311
02:26:57,600 --> 02:27:00,388
- Very happy.
- That's good.

1312
02:27:02,147 --> 02:27:07,108
I hope you don't mind the way I keep
going over this Barzini business.

1313
02:27:07,193 --> 02:27:10,106
- No, not at all.
- It's an old habit.

1314
02:27:11,698 --> 02:27:14,656
I spend my life trying not to be careless.

1315
02:27:16,119 --> 02:27:19,703
Women and children can be careless,
but not men.

1316
02:27:23,084 --> 02:27:25,291
- How's your boy?
- He's good.

1317
02:27:25,420 --> 02:27:28,287
He looks more like you every day.

1318
02:27:30,967 --> 02:27:35,256
He's smarter I am. He's three
and can read the funny papers.

1319
02:27:37,390 --> 02:27:39,472
Read the funny papers.

1320
02:27:46,775 --> 02:27:52,361
I want you to arrange for a telephone
man to check all in- and out-going calls.

1321
02:27:52,489 --> 02:27:55,777
I did it already.
I took care of that, Pop.

1322
02:27:55,867 --> 02:27:57,858
That's right. I forgot.

1323
02:28:01,873 --> 02:28:03,534
What's the matter?

1324
02:28:04,292 --> 02:28:06,374
What's bothering you?

1325
02:28:10,090 --> 02:28:14,675
I'll handle it. I told you
I can handle it, so I'll handle it.

1326
02:28:27,982 --> 02:28:32,351
I knew that Santino
would have to go through all this.

1327
02:28:32,487 --> 02:28:34,228
And Fredo...

1328
02:28:36,908 --> 02:28:38,899
Fredo was, well...

1329
02:28:40,787 --> 02:28:43,575
But I never wanted this for you.

1330
02:28:45,959 --> 02:28:51,045
I worked my whole life. I don't apologize
for taking care of my family.

1331
02:28:51,172 --> 02:28:55,040
And I refused to be a fool,

1332
02:28:55,176 --> 02:28:59,340
dancing on a string
held by all those big shots.

1333
02:29:01,266 --> 02:29:04,554
I don't apologize. That's my life,
but I thought that,

1334
02:29:06,396 --> 02:29:11,391
that when it was your time, you would
be the one to hold the strings.

1335
02:29:13,361 --> 02:29:18,982
Senator Corleone. Governor Corleone.
Something.

1336
02:29:19,075 --> 02:29:22,067
Another <i>pezzonovante.</i>

1337
02:29:22,203 --> 02:29:23,739
Well...

1338
02:29:27,041 --> 02:29:31,000
Just wasn't enough time, Michael.
Wasn't enough time.

1339
02:29:31,087 --> 02:29:34,455
We'll get there, Pop. We'll get there.

1340
02:29:39,512 --> 02:29:43,847
Now listen, whoever comes to you
with this Barzini meeting,

1341
02:29:43,933 --> 02:29:46,846
he's the traitor. Don't forget that.

1342
02:30:03,828 --> 02:30:05,944
Can I hold it, please?

1343
02:30:21,095 --> 02:30:24,963
- Can I water these?
- Yes, go ahead.

1344
02:30:25,099 --> 02:30:27,761
Over here, over here.

1345
02:30:29,646 --> 02:30:32,263
Be careful. You're spilling it.

1346
02:30:36,110 --> 02:30:37,646
(ANTHONY LAUGHING)

1347
02:30:38,488 --> 02:30:40,399
Anthony!

1348
02:30:40,532 --> 02:30:42,148
Come here, come here.

1349
02:30:47,330 --> 02:30:49,913
That's it. We'll put it right there.

1350
02:30:51,584 --> 02:30:52,699
(SIGHING)

1351
02:30:55,213 --> 02:30:57,671
I'll show you something. Come here.

1352
02:30:59,759 --> 02:31:01,591
Stand there.

1353
02:31:05,515 --> 02:31:07,222
Give me an orange!

1354
02:31:10,562 --> 02:31:11,723
(GROWLING)

1355
02:31:13,773 --> 02:31:15,309
(ANTHONY CRYING)

1356
02:31:15,400 --> 02:31:17,107
(VITO LAUGHING)

1357
02:31:25,410 --> 02:31:27,367
That's a new trick.

1358
02:31:28,413 --> 02:31:30,575
You run in there. Run in there.

1359
02:31:43,052 --> 02:31:44,167
(VITO LAUGHING)

1360
02:31:44,262 --> 02:31:46,173
ANTHONY: Where are you?

1361
02:31:51,644 --> 02:31:52,805
(COUGHING)

1362
02:31:54,022 --> 02:31:55,604
(ANTHONY LAUGHING)

1363
02:32:00,612 --> 02:32:02,603
(COUGHING CONTINUES)

1364
02:32:07,160 --> 02:32:08,742
(ANTHONY LAUGHING)

1365
02:32:16,044 --> 02:32:17,455
(ANTHONY EXCLAIMING)

1366
02:32:23,509 --> 02:32:25,216
(ANTHONY CHATTERING)

1367
02:32:39,317 --> 02:32:40,682
(BELL TOLLING)

1368
02:34:43,733 --> 02:34:46,191
Mike, can I have a minute?

1369
02:34:56,329 --> 02:34:58,616
Baum wants to arrange a meeting.

1370
02:34:58,748 --> 02:35:02,116
He says we can straighten out
any of our problems.

1371
02:35:02,710 --> 02:35:04,951
- You talked to him?
- Yeah.

1372
02:35:06,380 --> 02:35:10,123
I can arrange security. On my territory.

1373
02:35:13,221 --> 02:35:15,838
All right?
- All right.

1374
02:35:33,241 --> 02:35:36,233
Do you know
how they're going to come at you?

1375
02:35:38,871 --> 02:35:42,455
They're arranging a meeting
in Brooklyn. Tessio's ground.

1376
02:35:44,669 --> 02:35:46,376
Where I'll be safe.

1377
02:35:58,683 --> 02:36:02,176
I always thought it would be Clemenza,
not Tessio.

1378
02:36:02,270 --> 02:36:06,059
It's the smart move.
Tessio was always smarter.

1379
02:36:08,317 --> 02:36:09,682
But I'm going to wait.

1380
02:36:10,278 --> 02:36:11,313
After the baptism.

1381
02:36:15,116 --> 02:36:18,905
I've decided to be godfather
to Connie's baby.

1382
02:36:19,036 --> 02:36:22,904
And then I'll meet
with Don Barzini and Tattaglia.

1383
02:36:24,667 --> 02:36:27,625
All the heads of the five families.

1384
02:36:30,923 --> 02:36:32,505
(ORGAN PLAYING)

1385
02:36:35,511 --> 02:36:36,876
(BABY CRYING)

1386
02:36:53,571 --> 02:36:55,312
(RECITING IN LATIN)

1387
02:37:25,895 --> 02:37:27,556
<i>(RECITING CONTINUES)</i>

1388
02:38:48,561 --> 02:38:51,223
PRIEST: Michael, do you believe in God,
the Father,

1389
02:38:51,355 --> 02:38:53,596
Creator of Heaven and Earth?

1390
02:38:53,691 --> 02:38:54,852
I do.

1391
02:38:54,984 --> 02:38:58,227
<i>Do you believe in Jesus Christ,
His only Son, our Lord?</i>

1392
02:38:58,362 --> 02:38:59,443
<i>MICHAEL: I do.</i>

1393
02:38:59,572 --> 02:39:03,657
<i>PRIEST: Do you believe in the
Holy Ghost, the Holy Catholic Church?</i>

1394
02:39:03,784 --> 02:39:05,070
<i>MICHAEL: I do.</i>

1395
02:39:05,202 --> 02:39:07,364
<i>(RECITING CONTINUES IN LATIN)</i>

1396
02:39:37,985 --> 02:39:39,521
<i>(BABY CRYING)</i>

1397
02:39:39,695 --> 02:39:41,402
<i>(RECITING CONTINUES)</i>

1398
02:40:10,518 --> 02:40:14,933
PRIEST: Michael Francis Rizzi,
do you renounce Satan?

1399
02:40:21,028 --> 02:40:22,314
I do renounce him.

1400
02:40:32,164 --> 02:40:33,450
And all his works?

1401
02:40:41,966 --> 02:40:43,752
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

1402
02:40:47,304 --> 02:40:48,339
I do renounce them.

1403
02:40:50,057 --> 02:40:51,343
WOMAN: Oh, God!

1404
02:40:54,270 --> 02:40:58,104
- And all his pomps?
- I do renounce them.

1405
02:41:13,789 --> 02:41:18,033
Michael Rizzi, will you be baptized?

1406
02:41:18,169 --> 02:41:19,204
I will.

1407
02:41:19,420 --> 02:41:21,206
(RECITING IN LATIN)

1408
02:41:26,343 --> 02:41:31,964
Michael Rizzi, go in peace,
and may the Lord be with you. Amen.

1409
02:41:32,516 --> 02:41:34,348
(CHURCH BELLS RINGING)

1410
02:41:37,229 --> 02:41:39,015
(ALL CHATTERING)

1411
02:41:46,238 --> 02:41:48,070
Kay!

1412
02:41:48,199 --> 02:41:50,156
Kiss your godfather.

1413
02:42:02,046 --> 02:42:03,252
(INAUDIBLE)

1414
02:42:14,433 --> 02:42:18,552
Can't go to Vegas.
Something's come up.

1415
02:42:18,646 --> 02:42:20,228
Everybody has to leave without us.

1416
02:42:20,356 --> 02:42:23,348
- CONNIE: Mike, it's our first vacation!
- Connie, please.

1417
02:42:23,442 --> 02:42:27,060
Go back to the house, wait for my call.
It's important.

1418
02:42:28,197 --> 02:42:30,404
I'll only be a couple of days.

1419
02:42:46,799 --> 02:42:49,040
We're on our way to Brooklyn.

1420
02:42:51,262 --> 02:42:54,971
- I hope Mike can get us a good deal.
- I'm sure he will.

1421
02:43:02,690 --> 02:43:08,151
Sal, Tom, the boss says he'll come in a
separate car, so you two go on ahead.

1422
02:43:08,237 --> 02:43:11,775
- That screws up my arrangements.
- That's what he said.

1423
02:43:11,865 --> 02:43:14,072
I can't go either, Sal.

1424
02:43:26,046 --> 02:43:29,880
Tell Mike it was only business.
I always liked him.

1425
02:43:31,510 --> 02:43:34,252
- He understands that.
Excuse me, Sal.

1426
02:43:40,269 --> 02:43:42,886
Tom, can you get me off the hook?

1427
02:43:44,106 --> 02:43:47,315
- For old times' sake?
- Can't do it, Sally.

1428
02:44:18,682 --> 02:44:20,264
(TELEPHONE BEING DIALLED)

1429
02:44:32,613 --> 02:44:35,321
You have to answer for Santino, Carlo.

1430
02:44:40,245 --> 02:44:44,330
- Mike, you got it all wrong.
- You fingered Sonny for Barzini.

1431
02:44:45,209 --> 02:44:49,294
That little farce
you played with my sister.

1432
02:44:49,380 --> 02:44:54,250
- You think that could fool a Corleone?
- I'm innocent. I swear on the kids.

1433
02:44:54,343 --> 02:44:57,256
- Please, don't do this.
- Sit down.

1434
02:44:59,848 --> 02:45:02,180
Don't do this to me, please.

1435
02:45:11,276 --> 02:45:13,142
Barzini is dead.

1436
02:45:15,322 --> 02:45:17,484
So is Philip Tattaglia.

1437
02:45:18,784 --> 02:45:20,366
Moe Greene.

1438
02:45:21,328 --> 02:45:25,071
Strachi. Cuneo.

1439
02:45:27,000 --> 02:45:32,120
Today I settle all family business,
so don't tell me you're innocent, Carlo.

1440
02:45:32,256 --> 02:45:34,167
Admit what you did.

1441
02:45:38,137 --> 02:45:39,719
Get him a drink.

1442
02:45:46,103 --> 02:45:47,434
Come on.

1443
02:45:48,564 --> 02:45:51,147
Don't be afraid, Carlo.

1444
02:45:51,233 --> 02:45:54,100
Do you think
I'd make my sister a widow?

1445
02:45:55,195 --> 02:45:57,903
I'm godfather to your son, Carlo.

1446
02:46:04,746 --> 02:46:06,783
Go ahead, drink, drink.

1447
02:46:11,545 --> 02:46:15,334
No, you're out of the family business.
That's your punishment.

1448
02:46:16,425 --> 02:46:20,384
You're finished.
I'm putting you on a plane to Vegas.

1449
02:46:20,512 --> 02:46:22,253
Tom.

1450
02:46:26,435 --> 02:46:30,019
I want you to stay there. Understand?

1451
02:46:30,147 --> 02:46:32,559
Only don't tell me you're innocent.

1452
02:46:33,817 --> 02:46:38,186
Because it insults my intelligence.
Makes me very angry.

1453
02:46:42,451 --> 02:46:44,317
Who approached you?

1454
02:46:45,621 --> 02:46:47,953
Tattaglia or Barzini?

1455
02:46:55,797 --> 02:46:57,413
It was Barzini.

1456
02:47:01,595 --> 02:47:03,302
Good.

1457
02:47:09,353 --> 02:47:13,438
There's a car waiting outside
to take you to the airport.

1458
02:47:13,565 --> 02:47:17,183
I'll call your wife
and tell her what flight you're on.

1459
02:47:21,490 --> 02:47:23,982
- Mike...
- Get out of my sight.

1460
02:47:50,102 --> 02:47:51,684
Hello, Carlo.

1461
02:47:55,107 --> 02:47:56,518
(GRUNTING)

1462
02:48:49,828 --> 02:48:51,444
(CONNIE SCREAMING)

1463
02:48:51,538 --> 02:48:54,656
- I'm trying to tell you...
- CONNIE: Mama, please!

1464
02:49:00,088 --> 02:49:01,294
(SOBBING)

1465
02:49:03,175 --> 02:49:05,212
Michael!

1466
02:49:05,344 --> 02:49:07,381
KAY: What is it?
CONNIE: Where is he?

1467
02:49:09,640 --> 02:49:14,806
Michael, you lousy bastard!
You killed my husband.

1468
02:49:14,936 --> 02:49:19,021
You waited until Papa died,
so nobody could stop you.

1469
02:49:19,107 --> 02:49:22,190
You blamed him for Sonny.
Everybody did.

1470
02:49:22,319 --> 02:49:28,031
But you never thought about me!
Now what are we going to do?

1471
02:49:28,158 --> 02:49:29,694
KAY: Connie.

1472
02:49:31,995 --> 02:49:34,612
CONNIE: Why do you think
he kept Carlo at the Mall?

1473
02:49:34,748 --> 02:49:37,581
He knew he was going to kill him.

1474
02:49:37,668 --> 02:49:43,084
And you stood godfather to our baby.
You lousy cold-hearted bastard!

1475
02:49:43,215 --> 02:49:47,300
Want to know how many men he had
killed with Carlo? Read the papers!

1476
02:49:47,386 --> 02:49:50,094
That's your husband,
that's your husband!

1477
02:49:51,848 --> 02:49:53,714
(CONNIE SPITTING)

1478
02:49:57,646 --> 02:49:58,727
(CONNIE SOBBING)

1479
02:49:59,690 --> 02:50:03,934
No! No, no...

1480
02:50:04,027 --> 02:50:07,486
Take her upstairs. Get her a doctor.

1481
02:50:11,118 --> 02:50:12,734
(MICHAEL SIGHS)

1482
02:50:28,635 --> 02:50:30,342
She's hysterical.

1483
02:50:34,766 --> 02:50:36,677
Hysterical.

1484
02:50:38,687 --> 02:50:40,348
Michael, is it true?

1485
02:50:42,315 --> 02:50:45,899
- Don't ask me about my business, Kay.
- Is it true?

1486
02:50:46,027 --> 02:50:48,689
Don't ask me about my business.
Enough!

1487
02:51:08,800 --> 02:51:10,416
All right.

1488
02:51:13,221 --> 02:51:14,882
This one time.

1489
02:51:18,894 --> 02:51:22,262
This one time
I'll let you ask me about my affairs.

1490
02:51:28,361 --> 02:51:29,647
Is it true?

1491
02:51:33,742 --> 02:51:35,403
Is it?

1492
02:51:37,120 --> 02:51:38,576
No.

1493
02:51:52,511 --> 02:51:55,378
I guess we both need a drink. Come on.

1494
02:52:09,778 --> 02:52:11,519
(GLASS CLINKING)

1495
02:52:26,753 --> 02:52:28,369
Don Corleone.

